### CSS Text Shadow

**text-shadow** adds shadow effects to text.

---

### Syntax

```css
text-shadow: offset-x offset-y blur-radius color;
```

| Value | Required | Description |
|-------|----------|-------------|
| `offset-x` | Yes | Horizontal offset (positive = right) |
| `offset-y` | Yes | Vertical offset (positive = down) |
| `blur-radius` | No | Blur amount (default 0 = sharp) |
| `color` | No | Shadow color (default = text color) |

---

### Basic Examples

```css
/* Simple shadow */
text-shadow: 2px 2px gray;

/* Blurred shadow */
text-shadow: 2px 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);

/* No offset, just blur (glow) */
text-shadow: 0 0 10px blue;
```

---

### Multiple Shadows

Separate with commas:

```css
text-shadow: 
  1px 1px 2px black,
  0 0 25px blue,
  0 0 5px darkblue;
```

---

### Common Effects

```css
/* Clean emboss effect */
text-shadow: 1px 1px 0 white, -1px -1px 0 #333;

/* Glow effect */
text-shadow: 0 0 10px #0ff, 0 0 20px #0ff;

/* 3D text */
text-shadow: 
  1px 1px 0 #ccc,
  2px 2px 0 #999,
  3px 3px 0 #666,
  4px 4px 0 #333;

/* Subtle shadow for readability */
text-shadow: 1px 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);

/* Letterpress effect */
text-shadow: 0 1px 1px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
```

---

### Neon Glow

```css
.neon {
  color: #fff;
  text-shadow:
    0 0 7px #fff,
    0 0 10px #fff,
    0 0 21px #fff,
    0 0 42px #0fa,
    0 0 82px #0fa,
    0 0 92px #0fa,
    0 0 102px #0fa,
    0 0 151px #0fa;
}
```

> **Best Practice:** Use subtle shadows for better readability on images. Overuse of text-shadow can hurt performance and readability.
